<!-- popup.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>YouTube Ad Detector</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>YouTube Ad Detector</h1>
  <p>This extension detects YouTube ads and reloads the page after 1 second.</p>
</body>
</html>


**Instructions on how to install the extension on Chrome browser:**

1.  **Save the files:** Save the code above as `manifest.json`, `background.js`, and `popup.html` in a single folder.
2.  **Open Chrome Extensions page:** Open Chrome and type `chrome://extensions` in the address bar and press Enter.
3.  **Enable Developer Mode:** In the top left corner, toggle the "Developer mode" switch to ON.
4.  **Load Unpacked:** Click the "Load unpacked" button.
5.  **Select the folder:** Browse to the folder where you saved the `manifest.json`, `background.js`, and `popup.html` files and select it.
6.  **The extension is installed:** The YouTube Ad Detector extension should now appear in your Chrome extensions toolbar.